.TH "aio_port_set_rate" 9 "aio_port_set_rate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
aio_port_set_rate \- set sampling rate of LPCM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" aio_port_set_rate
.BI "(struct uniphier_aio_sub *sub "  ","
.BI "int rate "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sub" 12
the AIO substream pointer, PCM substream only
.IP "rate" 12
Sampling rate in Hz.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set suitable I2S format settings to input/output port block of AIO.
Parameter is specified by \fBhw_params\fP.

This function may return error if non-PCM substream.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, otherwise a negative value on error.
